<HTMLElementDfn>
<summary>
The <strong><c>&amp;lt;dfn&amp;gt;</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML">HTML</see> element is used to indicate the term being defined within the context of a definition phrase or sentence. The ancestor <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/p">p</see> element, the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dt">dt</see>/<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dd">dd</see> pairing, or the nearest <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/section">section</see> ancestor of the <c>&amp;lt;dfn&amp;gt;</c> element, is considered to be the definition of the term.
</summary>
